How many Democrats voted against adding seats to the Supreme Court? Not a single one.

It’s not enough that Democrats control the White House, Senate, and House of Representatives. They’re determined to control #SCOTUS, too.

I asked my colleagues to ensure that @SBAgov assistance can’t go to people found guilty of felony or misdemeanor rioting. Seems simple, smart, and fair—right?

Democrats banded together to defeat this common-sense step that supports job creators.

Freedom of religion is one of our most sacred liberties. There’s never a moment when we can take it for granted, least of all during a pandemic. I’m thankful to affirm that with 49 of my colleagues this evening.

Unfortunately, Democrats still blocked this amendment.

The Keystone XL pipeline supports American jobs, America’s energy independence, and America’s national security.

Why Pres. Biden shut it down and 48 Senate Democrats just voted to keep it closed is beyond me.

Late at night, Democrats voted to protect the SALT deduction for high-earners in blue states—only days after Pres. Biden unilaterally moved to kill 48,000 Louisiana jobs by 2022? 

You can’t make this this stuff up!

The question isn’t why the Senate had to pass an amendment to ensure that Pres. Biden’s EPA can’t ban fracking. We know that his war on energy jobs is plowing ahead. 

The question is why 43 Senate Democrats voted against our effort to save jobs that produce clean natural gas.

Withholding medical attention from babies who survive attempted abortions is murder. Senate Democrats just voted AGAINST holding health care workers who deny medical care to these babies accountable. 

Horrifying.

Pres. Biden’s ban on oil and gas leasing costs LA’s coastal restoration efforts big. 

Turns out students are casualties of the ban, too—and the Senate KNOWS it. 

I voted to recover funding for schools that lose $ to this moratorium. It’s insane Biden put kids in this position.

Sanctuary cities put communities at risk. 

Police need to be able to work with federal authorities to get dangerous criminals off the streets, but EVERY Senate Democrat just voted to fund states that refuse to let law enforcement do its job.

Our kids need to be back in schools. 

Senate Democrats just voted to send Covid $ to schools that choose to stay closed after teachers are vaccinated. 

This foolishness hurts students and helps no one.

If a state is under investigation for underreporting deaths in its nursing homes, why would we send tons more $ to its governor? 

You’d have to ask Senate Democrats. They voted against reducing funding for states making such epic mistakes.
